/awesome-broadcasting","categoryHTML":"<h2>LiveIP</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>See the <a href=\"#nmos\">NMOS</a> list for the AMWA Networked Media Open Specifications and open source implementations and tools.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-18T07:45:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ebu/awesome-broadcasting","categoryHTML":"<h2>NMOS</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/bbc/nmos-joint-ri\">BBC NMOS Joint Reference Implementation</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/bbc/nmos-joint-ri\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">7</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":7,\"repo\":\"bbc/nmos-joint-ri\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A Vagrant provisioning to build 4 virtual machines, an IS-04/IS-05 Node, IS-04 Registry, BCP-003-02 Authorisation Server, and the NMOS Testing Tool.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-18T07:45:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ebu/awesome-broadcasting","categoryHTML":"<h2>NMOS</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rhastie/easy-nmos\">Easy-NMOS</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/rhastie/easy-nmos\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">11</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":11,\"repo\":\"rhastie/easy-nmos\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A starter kit that allows the user to launch a simple NMOS setup with minimal installation steps, composed of three Docker containers: an NMOS Registry, a virtual NMOS Node, and the AMWA NMOS Testing Tool.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-18T07:45:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ebu/awesome-broadcasting","categoryHTML":"<h2>NMOS</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sony/nmos-cpp\">nmos-cpp</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sony/nmos-cpp\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">54</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":54,\"repo\":\"sony/nmos-cpp\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - An implementation of the AMWA Networked Media Open Specifications in C++, including an NMOS Registry and a toolkit and example of building an NMOS Node.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-18T07:45:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ebu/awesome-broadcasting","categoryHTML":"<h2>NMOS</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sony/nmos-js\">nmos-js</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sony/nmos-js\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">20</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":20,\"repo\":\"sony/nmos-js\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A simple browser-based NMOS Client/Controller with an IS-04 Registry browser and IS-05 Connection Management.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-18T07:45:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"vuejs/awesome-vue","categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>External Resources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://public.vuejsworkshops.com\">Vue.js Workshops</a> - Learn Vue 2, in browser, by building 3 applications: Landing page, Todos App and Podcasts aggregator.( Vue.js, Vue-Router, Vuex, Vue-Axios, Vue-Apollo )</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-18T07:31:59.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Party</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/135378/catan-explorers-pirates\">Catan: Explorers &#x26; Pirates Expansion</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Catan: Explorers &#x26; Pirates is the fourth major expansion for The Settlers of Catan. It includes five scenarios and three missions; some of the scenarios make use of the missions while others do not. This expansion is based on the CATAN base game rules but also contains a number of new game mechanisms. For example, ships are now equipped for expeditions and can be moved freely across the board. In the ships you transport settlers, crews, fish, or spices across the seas. The main goal is to build new outposts on the islands that are still undiscovered and to complete the Council of Catan's missions in the most skillful way possible. Catan: Explorers &#x26; Pirates differs from the Catan base game in three main ways. First, instead of having only a single island in the game on which players build and compete for resources, three islands are present. Second, instead of using cities, Catan: Explorers &#x26; Pirates allows players to build port settlements. Like cities, port settlements are worth two victory points (VPs), and the number of VPs required to win depends on the scenario. Third, if a player receives no resources during the production roll (other than on a roll of 7), she receives one gold in compensation. The winner is the first one who reaches 17 VPs.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://cf.geekdo-images.com/itemrep/img/mSwnoBBEdGDnzC5wlDVU9dhpIyA=/fit-in/246x300/filters:strip_icc()/pic2420310.jpg\" alt=\"Catan image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">2 - 4</td>\n<td align=\"right\">12+</td>\n<td align=\"right\">90-120m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2020-10-18T07:26:22.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1602979200000,"to":1603065599999,"previousId":"2020-10-19","nextId":"2020-10-17","nextName":"Oct 17th, 2020","previousName":"Oct 19th, 2020"}},"staticQueryHashes":["147714651","228695001","2744905544"]}